explanation:
memset - This is the string.h function actually called in the target function. To check MISRA compliance you must inspect its prototype/behavior and confirm the pointer and length arguments cannot cause out-of-bounds writes.

struct timespec (definition from <time.h>) - The memset call uses &ts and sizeof(ts). The exact layout/size of struct timespec is needed to verify that sizeof(ts) equals the actual object size and that writing sizeof(ts) bytes at &ts cannot overflow the ts object.

OS_Posix_CompAbsDelayTime - This function is passed &ts in the non-OS_CHECK branch. It could modify the contents of the ts object (and potentially use string.h functions internally). To be confident no out-of-bounds access related to string functions occurs, its implementation/signature must be inspected.

OS_CHECK - This macro/constant controls the branch that calls memset(&ts,...). Knowing its value and semantics is necessary to determine when memset is executed and whether ts is correctly initialized for that case (and to ensure no alternate code-paths lead to inconsistent object sizes or misuse).
